🔑 DSA Pattern / Concept
Pattern: Dynamic Programming (bounded knapsack, each item can be chosen once).

Why?

Each item has a weight and value.

You want to maximize value without exceeding capacity.

You must decide for each item: include it or exclude it.

This is the 0/1 Knapsack problem.

✅ Algorithm (DP Table)
Create a DP array dp[W+1] initialized to 0.

For each item (value, weight):

Traverse capacity w from W down to weight:

